<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25666</anchor> <rss>anon.172.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.172</addr>  <route>anon.172.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By the univalence principle for functions (<ref addr="erct-0015" href="erct-0015.xml" taxon="Axiom"/>), we may consider only the case that <tex>f  \equiv   1_{ A }</tex> and <tex>H  \equiv   1_{ 1_{ A } }</tex> exhibit the identity homotopy <tex>1_{ 1_{ 1_{ A } } } \colon   1_{ 1_{ A } }   \sim   1_{ 1_{ A } }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25667</anchor> <rss>erct-001W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001W</addr>  <route>erct-001W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Coherence for <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link> onto the identity</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001W.agda" type="external">erct-001W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>H  \colon  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> be a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> from <tex>f \colon  A  \to  A</tex> onto the identity function. Then we may construct a higher homotopy from <tex>H \circ  f</tex> to <tex>\mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ  H</tex>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25668</anchor> <rss>erct-0015.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0015</addr>  <route>erct-0015.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for dependent functions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0015.agda" type="external">erct-0015.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The reflexive graph structure on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex> by <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> and <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">identity homotopies</link> is <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>